  "narrative_arc": "Single mother living in a budget motel outside Disney World — technically homeless but not in a shelter, invisible to homelessness statistics. Baker documents the economics of motel poverty — weekly rates that exceed monthly rent, no kitchen, no lease protections, one paycheck from the street. When she turns to sex work to pay the motel, DCF comes for Moonee.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Halley's dome maps hidden homelessness — the motel economy that doesn't count as homeless but isn't housing. Her Layer 5 is the liminal space between shelter and home. Her dome reveals a population that no government system sees or serves.",
